The paper discusses the use of web usage mining to discover useful knowledge from user interactions with the web. This falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes the use of artificial ant colony clustering and linear genetic programming, which are both machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these techniques for creating adaptive web sites and network traffic flow analysis, which could fall under the categories of Databases (cs.DB) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
